From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 11:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: qcom: ipq5332: program system-NoC AXI-halt

On IPQ5332 the PCIe controller's AXI master is routed through the SoC
system NoC, which has a dedicated halt register the controller driver
must program ("axi-halt-val"). Without it, config-space TLPs succeed
during enumeration but stall the AXI bus once the link goes idle
afterwards -- e.g. when a driver (ath12k for the QCN6274) binds and reads
the endpoint's config space, hanging the SoC.

The vendor qti,pcie-ipq5332 node exposes this as a 6th reg region
"system_noc" (0x0059c210) plus an "axi-halt-val" property (0x1e). Other
qcom SoCs using cfg_2_9_0 (ipq6018/ipq8074/ipq9574) lack this reg and
handle the equivalent inside PARF, so the new reg is optional and the
quirk is a no-op when absent.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi
@@ -541,12 +541,15 @@
 			      <0x18000f20 0xa8>,
 			      <0x18001000 0x1000>,
 			      <0x00088000 0x3000>,
-			      <0x18100000 0x1000>;
+			      <0x18100000 0x1000>,
+			      <0x0059c210 0x4>;
 			reg-names = "dbi",
 				    "elbi",
 				    "atu",
 				    "parf",
-				    "config";
+				    "config",
+				    "system_noc";
+			axi-halt-val = <0x1e>;
 			device_type = "pci";
 			linux,pci-domain = <1>;
 			bus-range = <0x00 0xff>;
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-qcom.c
@@ -1178,7 +1178,10 @@ static int qcom_pcie_post_init_2_9_0(struct qcom_pcie *pcie)
 	struct dw_pcie *pci = pcie->pci;
 	u16 offset = dw_pcie_find_capability(pci, PCI_CAP_ID_EXP);
 	u32 val;
 	int i;
+	struct resource *noc_res;
+	void __iomem *noc;
+	u32 halt_val = 0x1e;

 	val = readl(pcie->parf + PARF_PHY_CTRL);
 	val &= ~PHY_TEST_PWR_DOWN;
@@ -1216,5 +1219,25 @@ static int qcom_pcie_post_init_2_9_0(struct qcom_pcie *pcie)
 	for (i = 0; i < 256; i++)
 		writel(0, pcie->parf + PARF_BDF_TO_SID_TABLE_N + (4 * i));

+	/*
+	 * IPQ5332: the PCIe master's AXI path on the system NoC needs the
+	 * "axi-halt-val" written to the external "system_noc" register, or
+	 * config TLPs stall the AXI bus once the link goes idle after
+	 * enumeration. Other qcom SoCs lack this reg and handle it in PARF.
+	 */
+	noc_res = platform_get_resource_byname(to_platform_device(pci->dev),
+					       IORESOURCE_MEM, "system_noc");
+	if (noc_res) {
+		noc = devm_ioremap(pci->dev, noc_res->start,
+				   resource_size(noc_res));
+		if (noc) {
+			of_property_read_u32(pci->dev->of_node, "axi-halt-val",
+					     &halt_val);
+			writel(halt_val, noc);
+			dev_info(pci->dev, "ipq5332: system_noc axi-halt-val=%#x\n",
+				 halt_val);
+		}
+	}
+
 	return 0;
 }
